nt and technology that now that be replaced to match the emerging facilities and technology elsewhere including the us the us specialty chemical industry especially in personal healthcare is gearing up to take back its pre dominance this has been allowed by development of green chemistries and the emergence of enzyme technology coming from advances in the food industry  the chinese did not see these changes in time their best hope is getting involved in joint ventures in the us and focus on growth and control of their own marketplace  michal grochol user pts maybe it is the chinese goal to acquire necessary knowhow and then get western companies from the chinese market by damaging their margins show more archives advertisement popular on wsj most popular videos goodbye sean spicer memorable moments from the podium california wildfire destroys homes near yosemite trumps statement on spicer departure spicer quits as scaramucci accepts white house job scaramucci says he regrets calling trump a hack most popular articles joseph rago wall street journal editorial writer dies at  jared kushner discloses dozens more assets in revised financial filing don’t be that guy avoiding over style pitfalls sean spicer resigns over objections to scaramucci hiring sean spicer faced myriad obstacles during dramatic rise and fall close chinese overcapacity leads saintgobain to eliminate product lines from useremail to message send an error has occurred please try again later thank you this article has been sent to save article sign in to save subscribe to wsj text size small medium large print facebook twitter whatsapp sms copy link compagnie de saintgobain sa private company information  bloomberg july    pm et building products company overview of compagnie de saintgobain sa snapshot people company overview compagnie de saintgobain sa designs manufactures and distributes building materials worldwide the company operates through innovative materials sector construction products sector and building distribution sector segments the innovative materials sector segment provides flat glass products such as float glass as well as laminated patterned silvered lacquered and coated glass and a range of products for the building industry including reinforced thermal insulation and acoustic protection glass solar control glass decorative safety and fireproof glass and active glass it also develops and supplies windshields including panoramic windshields sidelites backlites and gla compagnie de saintgobain sa designs manufactures and distributes building materials worldwide the company operates through innovative materials sector construction products sector and building distribution sector segments the innovative materials sector segment provides flat glass products such as float glass as well as laminated patterned silvered lacquered and coated glass and a range of products for the building industry including reinforced thermal insulation and acoustic protection glass solar control glass decorative safety and fireproof glass and active glass it also develops and supplies windshields including panoramic windshields sidelites backlites and glass sunroofs for automotive aeronautics and railway industries as well as for trucks and armored vehicles in addition this segment offers high valueadded solutions for the manufacturing construction transportation and healthcare markets comprising grains and powders abrasives glass fiber mesh for exterior wall insulation wall coverings joint tapes glass mat for thermal insulation and the production of asphalt concrete overlays as well as insect screen and paving reinforcement grids composites bearings and seals and fluid systems and lighting fabrics the construction products sector segment provides ductile cast iron pipe systems municipal castings hydraulic valves and wastewater and rainwater collection and drainage systems for buildings under the pam brand solutions for creating partition walls wall linings and ceiling systems thermal and acoustic insulation products and solutions mortarbased construction solutions under the weber brand exterior products and dry construction systems the building distribution sector segment distributes building materials to the renovation new building and home improvement markets the company was founded in  and is headquartered in courbevoie france detailed description  avenue dalsaceles miroirscourbevoie  francefounded in  employees wwwsaintgobaincom key executives for compagnie de saintgobain sa mr pierreandré de chalendar chairman  ceo age  total annual compensation €m compensation as of fiscal year  compagnie de saintgobain sa key developments saintgobain to increase its flat glass production capabilities in mexico jun   saintgobain has announced that it is building a new flat glass float production line in saltillo in mexico this plant scheduled to come on stream at the beginning of  will manufacture glass for the automotive and construction sectors it will meet the growing domestic demand and supply central america the caribbean and north america this investment will reinforce saintgobains position in building and automotive glass in mexico it will complement its manufacturing base in the region with the cuautla site already including two floats and their associated lines for mirrors and laminated glass one thinfilm coater line in operation and another under construction this new float line project in mexico marks a new step in the groups expansion strategy into highgrowth countries saintgobain in talks to acquire additional stake in glava jun   compagnie de saintgobain sa enxtpasgo is in exclusive talks about taking control of glava as saintgobain which already holds  of glavas capital is seeking to buy the shares of glavas founding families and shareholders compagnie de saintgobain sa approves dividend for  payable from june   jun   compagnie de saintgobain sa at its agm held on june   the shareholders approved the payment of an increased d